Title : Kimito Island Music Festival
Text : {{Notability|date=May 2014}}
[[File:Västanfjärd gamla kyrka.jpg|thumb|The [[Västanfjärd]] Old Church, one of the common venues in the festival.]]
The '''Kimito Island Music Festival''' ({{lang-sv|Kimitoöns Musikfestspel}}; {{lang-fi|Kemiönsaaren Musiikkijuhlat}}) is a [[chamber music]] festival that is held annually on [[Kimito]] Island in mid-July. The event features artists from [[Finland]] and abroad with a program ranging from classical to contemporary. The festival was founded in 1999 by pianist Martti Rautio and violinist Katinka Korkeala.<ref>[http://kauniaistenmusiikkijuhlat.fi/fi/esiintyjat/martti_rautio/ Martti Rautio - Kauniaisten musiikkijuhlat Grankulla musikfest] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150102193354/http://kauniaistenmusiikkijuhlat.fi/fi/esiintyjat/martti_rautio/ |date=2015-01-02 }}, kauniaistenmusiikkijuhlat.fi (Finnish)</ref> Katinka works as an artistic director. The position is shared by her twin sister, violinist [[Sonja Korkeala]], since 2008.<ref>[http://www.festivalnet.info/esittely/kemionsaaren-musiikkijuhlat/ Festivalnet - Kemiönsaaren musiikkijuhlat], festivalnet.info</ref> The executive director has been Jukka Mäkelä since 2009.<ref>[http://www.kimitomusicfestival.fi/info-en info - Kimitomusicfestival], kimitomusicfestival.fi</ref>

Among other performances, the festivals annually feature a premiere of a piece commissioned for the event by Finnish composers. Commissioned pieces have included works by [[Aulis Sallinen]],<ref>[http://www.hs.fi/kulttuuri/a1419915443749 Kuhmo-ilmiö Hiittisissä - Kulttuuri - Helsingin Sanomat], [[Helsingin Sanomat|hs.fi]]</ref> [[Kalevi Aho]],<ref>[http://www.hs.fi/arviot/Konsertti/a1353065199669 Schubert soi Ahon jousikvintetossa - Kulttuuri - Helsingin Sanomat], [[Helsingin Sanomat|hs.fi]]</ref> [[Jouni Kaipainen]] and [[Einojuhani Rautavaara]].<ref>[http://www.kimitomusicfestival.fi/kantaesitykset.html Kantaesitykset - Kimitomusikfestival], kimitomusicfestival.fi</ref>

The concert venues of the festival are medieval churches in [http://www.visitkimitoon.fi/en/seedo/to-see/kimito-kyrka Kimito] and [http://www.spottinghistory.com/view/84/sauvo-church/ Sauvo], and smaller churches in [http://www.spottinghistory.com/view/212/hiittinen-church/ Hiittinen], Dragsfjärd, [http://www.visitkimitoon.fi/en/seedo/to-see/vastanfjards-gamla-kyrka Västanfjärd] and Karuna. Other concert venues are the Söderlångvik manor house, which belonged to the Finnish patron Amos Anderson, the Sandö Manor House and the Salo Art Museum. Lunch and dinner concerts are held in The Westers Garden and Labbnäs Vacation Home.<ref>[http://www.kimitomusicfestival.fi/konserttipaikat Konserttipaikat - Kimitomusicfestival], kimitomusicfestival.fi</ref>

Kimito Island Music Festival is a member of Finland Festivals.<ref>[http://www.festivals.fi/en/festivaalit/kimito-island-music-festival/ Kimito Island Music Festival | Finland Festivals], festivals.fi</ref>
 
